{
  "stem": "19198.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 202.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the-- there was a lot of exchange of information so that we would do the most-- the best possible thing to hasten departure from Germany for Jews.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The-- or the movement, as such, also was-- and specifically the Hebrew Union College, together with the Jewish Theological Seminary in New York and what was then still a separate organization, the Jewish Institute of Religion, brought scholars to this country and, thus, saved the lives of many of the outstanding scholars and teachers of Judaism.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The best-known among the people who were brought to the Hebrew Union College was Abraham Joshua Heschel, who came first to the Hebrew Union College and later went to the Jewish Theological Seminary, which was a bit more sympathetic to his tradition in Judaism.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he-- he and Miriam and I became good friends during the time that he was at the college.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- which was my senior year of the college.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I-- we married at the-- after my junior year.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So the last year, I was-- we were married.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And were-- therefore, both of us got to know Dr.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Heschel.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not as such, because the-- there were specific Jewish organizations that were created for that purpose, the best-known of which is the JDC, which did the overseas work.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the HIAS, Hebrew Immigrant Aid Society, which, ever since the mass immigration in the early part of this century, had been the organization that worked with the government concerning immigration matters.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sure, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- I got to know him personally.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was the founder and the president of what was then still a separate seminary.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But Wise was a member of the same rabbinic organization.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, it was well-known that Wise had very close contact with Franklin Roosevelt.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
